Dow's 75-point fall led by losses in shares of Dow Inc., Verizon Communications Inc.

Shares of Dow Inc. and Verizon Communications Inc. are retreating Thursday morning, dragging the Dow Jones Industrial Average into negative territory. The Dow DJIA, +0.52% was most recently trading 79 points, or 0.3%, lower, as shares of Dow Inc. DOW, +2.36% and Verizon Communications Inc. VZ, +0.79% are contributing to the index's intraday decline. Dow Inc.'s shares are down $1.35, or 2.7%, while those of Verizon Communications Inc. are down $0.78, or 1.3%, combining for a roughly 14-point drag on the Dow. UnitedHealth UNH, -1.40%, Pfizer PFE, -0.48%, and Cisco CSCO, -0.05% are also contributing significantly to the decline. A $1 move in any of the index's 30 components results in a 6.78-point swing.